  <description type="morphology">Plants to 55 m. Winter buds usually glabrous. Leaves: blade base usually with 3–6 tubular basilaminar glands, apex short-acuminate, abaxial surface pilose at emergence; preformed blade with (6–)12–20(–30) teeth on each side; neoformed blade lengths usually distinctly greater than widths. Pedicels: lengths graded, shorter from base to apex, 1–13(–17 in fruit) mm. Capsules with thin, flexible valves.</description>
